      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BIG WEST (6) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing seventh (24.59) in a Grade 5 at Casino. The form from his last run stacks up well. Has ability and can bounce back. JUMP JERRY (7) was fast away and led throughout to score two back then was always well back and could manage only a 10 length 8th at this track (20.68) last time. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Key runner on best form. GREAT MARLOW (1) showed good pace from out wide and was prominent early but began to paddle and faded out of it when 5th at this track in Grade 5 company. Form here at the trip sound including six wins. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Can do much better this time. ROBELL CEASER (2) is another with top-three prospects.",
